 <div id="content_body">
	 <h1>YAPC::NA</h1>

<p>
YAPC (Yet Another Perl Conference) has been the Perl conference of choice for over a decade, it is hosted each year on five different continents. YAPC North America is the original YAPC that started it all.</p>
<p>
Hundreds of attendees come to hear over 100 talks across three days, but the YAPC's are primarily a social conference, and as such have a very community-driven down to Earth feel that make a YAPC a joy to attend. As with all the best conferences the &quot;hallway track&quot;, birds of a feather sessions (BOFs), and the people you meet are the reason most attendees come back year after year.</p>
<h3 id="2012_the_wild_side_of_perl">2012: The Wild Side of Perl</h3>
<p>
The <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/">2012 YAPC North America<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "2012 YAPC North America"<http://yapcna.org/> --></a> <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/conference">(Yet Another Perl Conference)<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "(Yet Another Perl Conference)"<http://yapcna.org/conference> --></a> will be held on the 13-15th June at <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/7072246690/yapc-2012-venue-uw-madison">the University of Wisconsin's Madison Campus<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "the University of Wisconsin's Madison Campus"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/7072246690/yapc=-2012=-venue=-uw=-madison> --></a>.</p>
<p>
Like many other Perl events the team are running a wide range of activities including the usual conference dinner, Job Fair, Hallway Track, Workshops, Training and will take Sponsorship and have a call for speakers.</p>
<p>
However, the organisation committee for this year, led by JT Smith, are doing an industrious job and seeking to lead the way in managing the event so that it will be the best Perl Conference that America has seen and will sow strong seeds for future teams to build upon.</p>
<h4 id="building_on_a_great_success">Building on a great success...</h4>
<p>
The organisers for 2012 have decided on a whole range of improvements and additions to previous years events. these can be easily followed on the regularly updated <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/">conference blog<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "conference blog"<http://blog.yapcna.org/> --></a>, all of their enhancements and initiatives are too numerous to list, but they include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Moving <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/">YAPC::NA<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "YAPC::NA"<http://yapcna.org/> --></a>. to a permanent home website;</li>
<li><a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8416752276/act-being-converted-to-plack">Improving the Act software<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Improving the Act software"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8416752276/act=-being=-converted=-to=-plack> --></a> that powers the conference websites for Perl conferences;</li>
<li>Creating the <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8940577681/future-friend-of-perl">Future Friend of Perl<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Future Friend of Perl"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8940577681/future=-friend=-of=-perl> --></a>;</li>
<li>Holding the <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://www.yapcna.org/perl-tng">Perl: The Next Generation<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Perl: The Next Generation"<http://www.yapcna.org/perl=-tng> --></a> Initiative;</li>
<li>Changing the <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/13102310411/auction-replaced-with-raffle-at-yapc-na-2012">Auction to a Raffle<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Auction to a Raffle"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/13102310411/auction=-replaced=-with=-raffle=-at=-yapc=-na=-2012> --></a>;</li>
<li>Making a <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8810880932/and-our-theme-for-yapc-na-2012-is">comprehensive 'theme'<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "comprehensive 'theme'"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8810880932/and=-our=-theme=-for=-yapc=-na=-2012=-is> --></a> &quot;The Wild Side of Perl&quot;and providing lots of choice of how to work with that theme and expound upon it;</li>
<li>Encouraging alternative travel, <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/13289305024/take-a-badger-bus-to-yapc?ad54a6c0">travel by bus<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "travel by bus"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/13289305024/take=-a=-badger=-bus=-to=-yapc?ad54a6c0> --></a>, or <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/13388191288/you-should-take-amtrak-to-more-places">travel by rail<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "travel by rail"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/13388191288/you=-should=-take=-amtrak=-to=-more=-places> --></a> to YAPC::NA;</li>
<li>Having a <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/12165676182/yapc-perl-documentary-commercial">Documentary Commercial<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Documentary Commercial"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/12165676182/yapc=-perl=-documentary=-commercial> --></a>;</li>
<li>Having a <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/10268761624/zero-to-perl-workshop">Zero - Perl Workshop<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Zero =- Perl Workshop"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/10268761624/zero=-to=-perl=-workshop> --></a>;</li>
<li>A best-ever job fair&quot;<a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/job-fair">http://yapcna.org/job-fair</a>';</li>
<li>Having a <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="https://www.facebook.com/yapcna">Facebook Page<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Facebook Page"<https://www.facebook.com/yapcna> --></a>;</li>
<li>Having a <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="https://twitter.com/#!/yapcna">Twitter Feed<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Twitter Feed"<https://twitter.com/#!/yapcna> --></a>;</li>
</ul>
<p>
There are many others such as the Partner Program and <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/sponsorship">initiatives for Sponsors<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "initiatives for Sponsors"<http://yapcna.org/sponsorship> --></a> and the varying <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/sponsorship/levels-of-sponsorship">levels of sponsorship<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "levels of sponsorship"<http://yapcna.org/sponsorship/levels=-of=-sponsorship> --></a> available for the event and the rights and privileges that come with it. This year they hope to make it very easy for many more companies and individuals to <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://yapcna.org/sponsorship/become-a-sponsor">become a sponsor<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "become a sponsor"<http://yapcna.org/sponsorship/become=-a=-sponsor> --></a>. There are several levels of Sponsorship:</p>
<ul>
<li>Friend of Perl</li>
<li><a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8940577681/future-friend-of-perl">Future Friend of Perl<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Future Friend of Perl"<http://blog.yapcna.org/post/8940577681/future=-friend=-of=-perl> --></a></li>
<li>Bronze</li>
<li>Silver</li>
<li>Gold</li>
<li>Platinum</li>
<li>Diamond</li>
</ul>
<p>
All of the sponsorship goes towards making a better conference or towards sponsoring a student place as part of the <a target="_blank" title="(external link)" href="http://www.yapcna.org/perl-tng">Perl: The Next Generation<!-- wiki-renamed-hyperlink "Perl: The Next Generation"<http://www.yapcna.org/perl=-tng> --></a> Initiative.</p>
<div class="wafl_block"><div>A full list of sponsors is shown on the website pages and will be in the
  associated media for the conference, including t-shirts, booklets, flyers.
  Currently these companies sponsor YAPC::NA: <span
    style="
margin: 10px auto 10px auto;
">
    <iframe src="http://www.yapcna.org/sponsors-folder?func=ajaxInlineView"
      id="sponsors-iframe"></iframe>
  </span></div>
<!-- wiki:
.html
